DIGEST
SB 176 Original 2026 Regular Session Allain
Present law provides that complaints about prescribed burns must be made to the
commissioner, who will investigate such complaints and who possesses the authority to
suspend or revoke authorization for the prescribed burn issued to persons found to be in
violation of the prescribed burn requirements or rules and regulations.
Proposed law retains present law and further clarifies that after an investigation, the
commissioner may suspend or revoke authorization for the prescribed burn for persons found
in violation.
Effective on August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 3:17(F))
